meek machine from the people who brought you `` 50 first dates '' comes this synthetic remake of the 1974 burt reynolds-robert aldrich crowdpleaser . instead of a hard-edged prison population , we get caricatures and stereotypes . adam sandler is far more convincing as happy gilmore than paul `` the wrecking '' crewe . though a brilliant stand-up comedian , chris rock has yet to find his cinematic niche . the only bright spots are reynolds ( in the michael conrad role ) and courteney cox